cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.SI 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with the regularization properties of Dropout and its extensions, which are popular heuristics for training neural networks. It may also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) as these fields heavily rely on neural networks and their training. Additionally, it may belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as these fields also use neural networks and their optimization techniques.
